# Cottage Cheese Snacks

{ rating="0" image="None" }
:::
:::

## Scrambled Eggs

Stir 2–3 Tbsp cottage cheese into beaten eggs before cooking.
Makes them fluffier and more filling.
Season as usual.

## Dip or Spread

Blend cottage cheese with 1 garlic clove, 1 Tbsp lemon juice, and fresh herbs (parsley, oregano, chives).
Use as a dip for vegetables or pita, or spread on toast.

## Toast

Spread on toast with sliced tomato, a drizzle of olive oil, and salt.
Add everything bagel seasoning or red pepper flakes.

## Smoothies

Add 1/4 cup to a smoothie in place of or alongside Greek yogurt.
Blends smooth, minimal flavor impact.

## Notes

- Blending cottage cheese first eliminates the curd texture if that’s a concern
- Full-fat cottage cheese has a richer flavor; low-fat works fine in cooked applications
